qas.question: What architecture type came after Norman in England?
What architecture type came before Norman in England?
What place had the Norman Arab architectural style?
What precedes the period of Anglo-Saxon architecture?
What architecture type came after Early Gothic?
Who incorperated Islamic, LOmbard, and Byzantine building techniques in England?

context: In England, the period of Norman architecture immediately succeeds that of the Anglo-Saxon and precedes the Early Gothic. In southern Italy, the Normans incorporated elements of Islamic, Lombard, and Byzantine building techniques into their own, initiating a unique style known as Norman-Arab architecture within the Kingdom of Sicily.
